CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 15, 1958, pg. 5, reads: "Public Affairs Are His Affair - Wendell L. Wray heads the public affairs division of Carnegie Library. He keeps abreast of the times by reading current newspapers and literature, studying contemporary foreign-language novels, and by public speaking and TV appearances.  He is a magna cum laude graduate of Bates College in Maine. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of librarian Wendell Wray posed behind large globe in Carnegie Library of Pittsburgh
